Botium Toys, Scope, Goals, and risk Assessment report


SCORE AND GOALS OF THE AUDIT

Scope: The scope of this audit is define as the entire security program at Botium Toys. This includes their assets like employee 
equipment and devices, their internal network, and their systems. Review the assets Botium Toys has and the contrls and compliance 
practice they have in place. 


Goals: Asses existing assets and complete the controls and compliance checklist to determine which controls and compliance best
practices that need to be implemented to improve Botium Toyr's security posture.


CURRENT ASSETS

Assets managed by the IT Department include:
● On-premises equipment for in-office business needs
● Employee equipment: end-user devices (desktops/laptops, smartphones),
remote workstations, headsets, cables, keyboards, mice, docking stations, 
surveillance cameras, etc.
● Storefront products available for retail sale on site and online; stored in the 
company's adjoining warehouse
● Managment of systems, software, and services: accounting, 
telecommunication, database, security, ecommerce, and inventory management
● Internet access
● Internal network
● Data retention and storage
● Legacy system maintenance: end-of-life systems that require human monitoring 


